CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 19, 1960, pg. 12, reads:"Mark Fourth Anniversary - The Y-Phalanx of the Centre Avenue YMCA will celebrate its fourth anniversary March 20-27. The program will be as follows: Sunday, church service; Monday, open house; Tuesday, vesper service; Wednesday, "Splash Party;" Thursday, bowling; Friday, entertain lady guests; Sunday, banquet, with Atty. Byrd Brown, the Rev. James Cayce and the Rev. Cornell Talley as guests.  Front row, left to right; Donald Richardson, tribune; Bernard Clark, dean of pledges; Donald McCreary, primas; R.C. Jones, D.Charley and Kenneth Nelson.  Back row: Russell T. Washington, mentor; Gordon Hawthorne, social chairman; James Davis, quaestor; Leroy Lowery, pro-primas, and Charles Stanback. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Y-Phalanx members, front row, from left: Donald Richardson, Bernard Clark, Donald McCreary, R. C. Jones, D. Charley, Kenneth Nelson; back row: Russell T. Washington, Gordon Hawthorne, James Davis, Leroy Lowery, and Charles Stanback, posed in Centre Avenue YMCA, another version
